1
00:00:03,772 --> 00:00:04,740
(This drama is a work of fiction.)

2
00:00:04,740 --> 00:00:06,141
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

3
00:00:06,141 --> 00:00:07,209
(Scenes with child actors
followed production guidelines.)

4
00:00:07,776 --> 00:00:11,213
(Free supply of premium fertilizer)

5
00:00:11,213 --> 00:00:13,315
(Mat Story win-win partnership,
Free supply of premium fertilizer)

6
00:00:13,315 --> 00:00:17,286
(Free supply of premium fertilizer)

7
00:00:17,286 --> 00:00:20,889
Yeonri-ri residents.
Mat Story is giving away...

8
00:00:20,889 --> 00:00:22,658
premium fertilizer for free.

9
00:00:22,658 --> 00:00:24,359
Please come quickly and pick it up.

10
00:00:24,359 --> 00:00:26,361
Yes, it's free. Take as much as you like.

11
00:00:26,361 --> 00:00:28,464
Yes, please come.

12
00:00:28,931 --> 00:00:31,567
Sign right here.

13
00:00:31,567 --> 00:00:32,534
Yes.

14
00:00:33,035 --> 00:00:34,069
Please come.

15
00:00:34,069 --> 00:00:36,939
Please come. This way.

16
00:00:38,507 --> 00:00:40,242
Yes, right here.

17
00:00:41,677 --> 00:00:43,479
Just sign here and take them.

18
00:00:44,046 --> 00:00:45,414
Please take them.

19
00:00:46,515 --> 00:00:47,750
(Free fertilizer distribution list
for Yeonri-ri branch)

20
00:00:47,950 --> 00:00:48,984
Thank you.

21
00:00:48,984 --> 00:00:50,486
Yes, take as much as you want.

22
00:00:50,486 --> 00:00:51,854
Free fertilizer...

23
00:00:51,854 --> 00:00:55,858
directly provided by Manager Seong Tae Hun
of Mat Story.

24
00:00:56,558 --> 00:00:58,060
Come and get it.

25
00:01:00,562 --> 00:01:02,131
You came.

26
00:01:02,131 --> 00:01:03,565
Right here.

27
00:01:03,565 --> 00:01:06,201
Here are your names.
Deok Rae, Ok Rae, and Mak Rae.

28
00:01:10,572 --> 00:01:11,507
Thank you.

29
00:01:11,507 --> 00:01:13,409
No, I'm the one who should be grateful.
You're here.

30
00:01:13,409 --> 00:01:15,744
- Is it really okay to take this?
- Yes, it's fine.

31
00:01:15,744 --> 00:01:16,612
Have faith.

32
00:01:17,446 --> 00:01:19,848
Trust your village chief and take it.

33
00:01:19,848 --> 00:01:20,783
You're here.

34
00:01:21,049 --> 00:01:22,251
Did you make kimchi?

35
00:01:23,752 --> 00:01:25,020
Do you not use fermented seafood?

36
00:01:29,858 --> 00:01:32,094
Please sign here.

37
00:01:36,765 --> 00:01:37,633
Seong Tae Hun.

38
00:01:38,434 --> 00:01:39,368
Make sure you do this right.

39
00:01:40,369 --> 00:01:41,737
If you betray us again...

40
00:01:41,737 --> 00:01:44,306
or our cabbages die
because of that fertilizer,

41
00:01:44,740 --> 00:01:45,674
I won't forgive you.

42
00:01:46,842 --> 00:01:48,010
Take two.

43
00:01:48,010 --> 00:01:49,278
It's okay.

44
00:01:49,278 --> 00:01:51,480
Take as much as you want.

45
00:01:52,081 --> 00:01:54,349
Don't worry about anything,

46
00:01:54,349 --> 00:01:55,284
Chief.

47
00:01:56,819 --> 00:01:58,854
If this goes wrong, you might end up
becoming the fertilizer yourself.

48
00:02:02,157 --> 00:02:03,792
That almost sounds like...

49
00:02:03,792 --> 00:02:05,661
you're saying you trust me.

50
00:02:06,095 --> 00:02:08,330
Everyone in Yeonri-ri showed up
because they all trust you.

51
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:13,135
I still don't trust Mat Story.

52
00:02:13,736 --> 00:02:14,503
But...

53
00:02:15,404 --> 00:02:17,039
I'm willing to trust you, Tae Hun.

54
00:02:23,479 --> 00:02:25,013
I'm scared of the saying,

55
00:02:25,013 --> 00:02:26,882
"You reap what you sow."

56
00:02:28,217 --> 00:02:30,185
If I plant evil in someone's heart,

57
00:02:30,786 --> 00:02:32,187
a knife will grow there.

58
00:02:33,255 --> 00:02:34,823
And that knife will eventually stab me.

59
00:02:36,825 --> 00:02:38,761
Just as a farmer must not deceive
the land,

60
00:02:38,761 --> 00:02:40,562
a person must not deceive another.

61
00:02:41,330 --> 00:02:43,232
What sprouts from that heart...

62
00:02:44,266 --> 00:02:45,801
Whether it grows into good fruit...

63
00:02:47,035 --> 00:02:48,804
or rots and stinks...

64
00:02:50,239 --> 00:02:52,074
It'll all be up to you now, okay?

65
00:02:54,009 --> 00:02:55,978
(EP 9)

66
00:02:55,978 --> 00:03:02,851
(You Reap What You Sow,
and Anxiety Doubles When Buried)

67
00:03:05,387 --> 00:03:08,223
Did you all bring seeds from home?

68
00:03:08,223 --> 00:03:09,391
Yes.

69
00:03:09,391 --> 00:03:11,427
Then plant them nicely in a pot...

70
00:03:11,427 --> 00:03:13,695
and write your name on a tag.

71
00:03:13,695 --> 00:03:14,930
Okay.

72
00:03:35,818 --> 00:03:37,386
You can plant these.

73
00:03:38,554 --> 00:03:40,856
But they are yours.

74
00:03:40,856 --> 00:03:43,025
What's yours and mine?

75
00:03:43,025 --> 00:03:44,593
We'll plant them together.

76
00:03:47,496 --> 00:03:49,765
Really? Thanks.

77
00:03:54,570 --> 00:03:56,038
How's it going?

78
00:03:57,473 --> 00:04:00,476
Go scoop some soil from the back
for your pots.

79
00:04:00,476 --> 00:04:01,543
Okay.

80
00:04:04,046 --> 00:04:05,447
Don't take too much though.

81
00:04:18,827 --> 00:04:20,529
Do you want some seeds?

82
00:04:53,328 --> 00:04:56,698
What was your name again?

83
00:04:57,533 --> 00:04:59,168
Wu Ju. Han Wu Ju.

84
00:05:01,937 --> 00:05:03,739
Wu Ju. It's written here.

85
00:05:04,306 --> 00:05:06,909
Well, my name is...

86
00:05:10,379 --> 00:05:11,680
Seong Ji Sang.

87
00:05:17,453 --> 00:05:18,720
I know.

88
00:05:20,556 --> 00:05:22,357
So you remembered my name.

89
00:05:54,156 --> 00:05:55,591
What are you doing?

90
00:05:56,158 --> 00:05:56,959
What?

91
00:05:59,294 --> 00:06:00,395
Just getting water.

92
00:06:00,395 --> 00:06:02,631
Seong Tae Hun, be sure
to handle that fertilizer right.

93
00:06:02,631 --> 00:06:05,234
I'll be watching you like a hawk.

94
00:06:27,489 --> 00:06:28,357
Ji Cheon.

95
00:06:28,957 --> 00:06:29,792
Bo Mi.

96
00:06:30,959 --> 00:06:32,161
I'm sorry.

97
00:06:32,161 --> 00:06:34,963
I've caused trouble for you
and your family too.

98
00:06:34,963 --> 00:06:36,098
It's a bit uncomfortable, right?

99
00:06:36,865 --> 00:06:37,766
No.

100
00:06:38,167 --> 00:06:41,070
Your mother is doing well with us,
so don't worry too much.

101
00:06:51,613 --> 00:06:53,315
Right. I have something for you.

102
00:06:54,283 --> 00:06:55,284
One second.

103
00:07:00,289 --> 00:07:01,223
What's this?

104
00:07:01,857 --> 00:07:02,724
Ta da.

105
00:07:05,060 --> 00:07:06,428
They look like matchsticks.

106
00:07:06,995 --> 00:07:09,131
These are marigold seeds.

107
00:07:09,598 --> 00:07:12,735
It symbolizes happiness
that will surely come.

108
00:07:14,303 --> 00:07:15,904
- Marigold?
- Yes.

109
00:07:16,739 --> 00:07:18,040
Plant these seeds,

110
00:07:18,907 --> 00:07:22,344
and believe that happiness
is coming your way too.

111
00:07:22,811 --> 00:07:25,981
These seeds will protect you here.

112
00:07:27,249 --> 00:07:28,283
I'll definitely plant them.

113
00:07:28,684 --> 00:07:31,286
I'll water it every day and check on it.

114
00:07:32,020 --> 00:07:33,088
As if they were you.

115
00:07:34,189 --> 00:07:35,991
- Promise?
- Yes.

116
00:07:35,991 --> 00:07:37,326
- You mean it?
- Yes.

117
00:07:41,549 --> 00:07:44,812
(Yeonri-ri Village)

118
00:08:16,532 --> 00:08:17,766
Plant these seeds,

119
00:08:18,767 --> 00:08:22,037
and believe that happiness
is coming your way too.

120
00:08:34,516 --> 00:08:35,818
Let's see.

121
00:08:35,818 --> 00:08:37,953
Yeonri-ri no. 14, Go Ok Sun.

122
00:08:39,254 --> 00:08:42,424
No. 15-2, Choi Cheol Gi.

123
00:08:48,230 --> 00:08:50,065
No. 18-1.

124
00:08:50,732 --> 00:08:53,368
Lee Hui Sang, Yeonri Jungang-gil no. 1.

125
00:08:53,902 --> 00:08:55,437
Jang Pil Sun...

126
00:08:55,437 --> 00:08:56,405
Jang...

127
00:09:07,783 --> 00:09:09,485
Hello, Mr. Bae. This is Seong Tae Hun.

128
00:09:10,219 --> 00:09:12,187
Mr. Seong. You've been working hard.

129
00:09:13,055 --> 00:09:14,590
How are things in Yeonri-ri?

130
00:09:15,958 --> 00:09:19,728
The response to the free fertilizer
distribution has been very positive.

131
00:09:19,728 --> 00:09:21,663
People's perception...

132
00:09:21,663 --> 00:09:23,699
of Mat Story has improved as well.

133
00:09:27,269 --> 00:09:28,937
As expected of you, Mr. Seong.

134
00:09:29,271 --> 00:09:31,640
Winning people over isn't easy,

135
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:32,741
but you're the best at it.

136
00:09:33,642 --> 00:09:37,446
It's all thanks to your full support, sir.

137
00:09:37,913 --> 00:09:39,648
You know, people's hearts...

138
00:09:40,182 --> 00:09:41,917
It's hard to get past the threshold.

139
00:09:41,917 --> 00:09:44,453
But once you're in, they stop questioning.

140
00:09:48,824 --> 00:09:50,492
What do you mean by that?

141
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:53,529
If you need anything else, don't hesitate.

142
00:09:53,529 --> 00:09:55,831
Budget, supplies...
I'll fully support you.

143
00:09:56,598 --> 00:09:59,935
And be sure to organize
and submit the residents' list.

144
00:10:00,869 --> 00:10:02,404
It's all needed for support.

145
00:10:04,206 --> 00:10:07,476
Yes, I've stored it in the database.

146
00:10:08,210 --> 00:10:11,180
I'll think more about additional
support measures...

147
00:10:11,880 --> 00:10:13,215
and let you know later.

148
00:10:13,849 --> 00:10:15,617
Good. I trust you.

149
00:10:15,617 --> 00:10:17,653
I'll be in touch soon.

150
00:10:29,431 --> 00:10:31,633
Just as a farmer must not deceive
the land,

151
00:10:31,633 --> 00:10:33,335
a person must not deceive another.

152
00:10:34,470 --> 00:10:37,239
What sprouts from that heart...
Whether it grows into good fruit...

153
00:10:38,774 --> 00:10:40,609
or rots and stinks...

154
00:10:40,609 --> 00:10:42,878
It'll all be up to you now, okay?

155
00:11:00,696 --> 00:11:02,397
- What are you looking at?
- You scared me.

156
00:11:02,898 --> 00:11:03,799
What are you up to?

157
00:11:04,767 --> 00:11:06,835
Chief, you see...

158
00:11:07,836 --> 00:11:10,105
If you came to see your partner, go on in.

159
00:11:10,105 --> 00:11:11,607
No.

160
00:11:12,007 --> 00:11:14,576
Don't lie. I can tell by your face
that you're worried.

161
00:11:16,145 --> 00:11:18,247
I'll wait and see.

162
00:11:18,247 --> 00:11:19,281
Come on.

163
00:11:21,650 --> 00:11:25,521
My lovely Nam Hye Sun asked me
to give this to you.

164
00:11:26,822 --> 00:11:27,823
She didn't have to...

165
00:11:29,158 --> 00:11:31,427
Come with me. I'll deliver it myself.

166
00:11:31,427 --> 00:11:32,261
Deliver?

167
00:11:37,433 --> 00:11:39,301
Good night, honey.

168
00:11:44,873 --> 00:11:47,342
I brought some side dishes.

169
00:11:48,477 --> 00:11:49,678
So how about a drink?

170
00:11:50,512 --> 00:11:53,015
I'm sorry. I don't really drink,

171
00:11:53,315 --> 00:11:54,583
so there's no alcohol at home.

172
00:11:54,983 --> 00:11:55,851
I see.

173
00:11:56,952 --> 00:11:58,120
I figured that'd be the case.

174
00:12:00,923 --> 00:12:01,857
Ta da.

175
00:12:10,532 --> 00:12:12,000
Seon Ja, Dong Sik, and others...

176
00:12:12,434 --> 00:12:14,837
stopped by to give me food for the kids.

177
00:12:16,105 --> 00:12:18,140
Even the three sisters came by.

178
00:12:19,174 --> 00:12:23,045
They brought a ton again today
to thank me for the fertilizer.

179
00:12:25,814 --> 00:12:28,550
I can tell that Pil Sun brought
the stir-fried anchovies.

180
00:12:29,918 --> 00:12:31,153
This is how she fries them,

181
00:12:31,920 --> 00:12:33,055
even though her teeth are weak.

182
00:12:35,657 --> 00:12:37,326
And this...

183
00:12:37,826 --> 00:12:40,362
Hui Sang's father brought it.

184
00:12:41,663 --> 00:12:43,832
He always picks the peppers this way.

185
00:12:47,936 --> 00:12:49,004
It's salty.

186
00:12:50,806 --> 00:12:51,907
Just like his personality.

187
00:12:53,108 --> 00:12:55,210
Wow. I'm amazed.

188
00:12:55,210 --> 00:12:57,079
You recognize whose they are
even without name tags.

189
00:12:58,347 --> 00:13:01,316
These are name tags themselves.

190
00:13:03,419 --> 00:13:07,222
This kimchi was made from young radish...

191
00:13:07,689 --> 00:13:09,391
that got hit by hail last year...

192
00:13:09,391 --> 00:13:11,226
and were full of holes.

193
00:13:11,960 --> 00:13:13,962
Her husband has a bad back,

194
00:13:14,296 --> 00:13:15,497
so they couldn't harvest
the radishes on time.

195
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:20,669
All these dishes have stories behind them.

196
00:13:22,337 --> 00:13:23,739
That's how it is in Yeonri-ri.

197
00:13:24,640 --> 00:13:26,675
Just by looking at a single dish,

198
00:13:26,675 --> 00:13:28,777
you can tell how much it rained that year,

199
00:13:29,344 --> 00:13:32,181
or who's been sick.

200
00:13:34,483 --> 00:13:36,452
They live with their lives laid bare
like this,

201
00:13:36,452 --> 00:13:38,754
so how could I possibly turn
my back on them?

202
00:13:39,788 --> 00:13:41,023
The same goes for you now.

203
00:13:42,291 --> 00:13:43,625
Now that you've eaten this food,

204
00:13:44,393 --> 00:13:47,396
you've taken a piece of everyone
in Yeonri-ri.

205
00:13:47,396 --> 00:13:48,163
You got that?

206
00:13:54,703 --> 00:13:55,571
Yes.

207
00:14:02,044 --> 00:14:03,145
This is really nice.

208
00:14:14,456 --> 00:14:15,657
A few years ago,

209
00:14:17,226 --> 00:14:19,328
my Hye Sun got cancer.

210
00:14:20,662 --> 00:14:21,497
What?

211
00:14:22,965 --> 00:14:24,933
When I was told that my wife might die,

212
00:14:26,101 --> 00:14:27,536
everything went dark.

213
00:14:31,540 --> 00:14:33,675
'How can I live without my Hye Sun?'

214
00:14:35,377 --> 00:14:38,147
That thought made me want to die.

215
00:14:41,483 --> 00:14:42,885
After a few years,

216
00:14:43,685 --> 00:14:44,787
she fully recovered.

217
00:14:46,522 --> 00:14:49,391
Then I felt like I could live again.

218
00:14:50,893 --> 00:14:52,694
That's a relief.

219
00:14:55,831 --> 00:14:58,167
After surviving something like that,
we never fight anymore.

220
00:14:59,268 --> 00:15:01,904
There's not enough time,
even just to love.

221
00:15:06,175 --> 00:15:09,244
What about when you don't understand her?

222
00:15:10,846 --> 00:15:12,881
Honestly, that happens to me a lot.

223
00:15:13,949 --> 00:15:15,584
My wife says she suddenly
came back to Korea...

224
00:15:15,584 --> 00:15:18,253
because of Ji Sang.

225
00:15:18,253 --> 00:15:19,621
But I really don't understand.

226
00:15:20,189 --> 00:15:23,225
I feel like she's hiding something
from me.

227
00:15:25,727 --> 00:15:26,962
Seong Tae Hun.

228
00:15:28,497 --> 00:15:30,732
Do you think your wife
fully understands you?

229
00:15:31,900 --> 00:15:35,604
Trying to understand her
is a contradiction itself.

230
00:15:37,106 --> 00:15:38,607
Then what am I supposed to do?

231
00:15:39,174 --> 00:15:41,376
Understanding is done with your head,

232
00:15:42,211 --> 00:15:45,647
and love is done with your heart.

233
00:15:45,981 --> 00:15:47,850
Who in the world...

234
00:15:47,850 --> 00:15:50,052
loves with their head?

235
00:15:52,521 --> 00:15:53,655
With my heart.

236
00:15:59,061 --> 00:16:00,596
You should...

237
00:16:01,497 --> 00:16:03,999
take your wife home now.

238
00:16:04,600 --> 00:16:06,702
My wife and I are forced to live apart...

239
00:16:07,002 --> 00:16:08,637
because of you two.

240
00:16:10,572 --> 00:16:12,641
I've been sleeping alone
in the living room,

241
00:16:13,208 --> 00:16:15,144
so my back is killing me.

242
00:16:16,478 --> 00:16:18,113
I'm sorry, Chief.

243
00:16:18,380 --> 00:16:20,716
Goodbye. Don't cry.

244
00:16:20,716 --> 00:16:21,583
I won't.

245
00:16:21,884 --> 00:16:23,719
- Bye.
- Be safe.

246
00:16:36,865 --> 00:16:39,935
Ma'am. What are you doing here
at this hour?

247
00:16:43,972 --> 00:16:46,809
This is yours, right?

248
00:16:47,109 --> 00:16:47,976
This...

249
00:16:48,610 --> 00:16:51,013
It's my wife's. Where did you find it?

250
00:16:51,346 --> 00:16:53,682
Mak Rae thought...

251
00:16:54,083 --> 00:16:57,686
it was her youngest's stroller
and brought it home.

252
00:16:58,620 --> 00:16:59,822
I'm so sorry.

253
00:17:00,422 --> 00:17:01,457
Thank you. Bye.

254
00:17:14,403 --> 00:17:15,571
Goodness.

255
00:17:16,605 --> 00:17:17,806
Honey.

256
00:17:20,042 --> 00:17:21,877
Is this all you took with you?

257
00:17:30,786 --> 00:17:31,653
At least,

258
00:17:32,554 --> 00:17:34,623
you took the kids' pictures, Cho Mi Ryeo.

259
00:18:02,184 --> 00:18:03,118
This...

260
00:18:04,086 --> 00:18:05,053
This...

261
00:18:09,525 --> 00:18:10,392
Yes?

262
00:18:11,126 --> 00:18:12,127
You're not going to bed?

263
00:18:12,461 --> 00:18:14,663
I should.

264
00:18:22,438 --> 00:18:23,639
Isn't that Mom's medication?

265
00:18:25,207 --> 00:18:27,810
Is it okay if she doesn't take it
for a few days?

266
00:18:30,279 --> 00:18:32,981
It's not something she has to take
every single day.

267
00:18:34,483 --> 00:18:35,517
I learned that...

268
00:18:36,985 --> 00:18:39,054
panic disorder isn't caused
because the body is sick.

269
00:18:40,422 --> 00:18:42,157
It's a signal...

270
00:18:43,559 --> 00:18:45,194
that the mind can't hold on any longer.

271
00:18:49,398 --> 00:18:51,100
A signal that the mind can't
hold on anymore.

272
00:18:53,402 --> 00:18:54,403
Your mom...

273
00:18:56,972 --> 00:18:58,907
What do you think was so hard for her?

274
00:19:01,176 --> 00:19:03,078
What was she enduring...

275
00:19:05,347 --> 00:19:06,615
all by herself?

276
00:19:14,723 --> 00:19:16,959
(Yeonri-ri)

277
00:19:32,975 --> 00:19:33,942
What's that?

278
00:19:57,399 --> 00:19:59,268
What is this? It's not snow.

279
00:20:07,009 --> 00:20:07,910
What is this?

280
00:20:23,425 --> 00:20:24,827
My goodness. What is this?

281
00:20:33,602 --> 00:20:36,472
Chlorophyll levels are uniform.

282
00:20:44,780 --> 00:20:46,548
Moisture is fine.

283
00:20:50,652 --> 00:20:52,387
(Soil condition report)

284
00:20:54,256 --> 00:20:55,090
Good.

285
00:20:56,592 --> 00:20:57,659
Are you in there, Tae Hun?

286
00:20:57,659 --> 00:20:59,728
Are you there? Tae Hun.

287
00:20:59,728 --> 00:21:03,265
Come out to the field.

288
00:21:03,265 --> 00:21:04,366
Why?

289
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:05,768
- What is it?
- Come out here.

290
00:21:14,743 --> 00:21:16,912
What are you doing?

291
00:21:17,780 --> 00:21:20,482
It's happening here too.

292
00:21:20,883 --> 00:21:22,351
What are we going to do about this?

293
00:21:23,152 --> 00:21:24,887
- What is this?
- I thought it was just my field.

294
00:21:24,887 --> 00:21:25,854
But it's everywhere.

295
00:21:26,688 --> 00:21:27,556
Goodness.

296
00:21:32,261 --> 00:21:33,629
Look at this.

297
00:21:33,896 --> 00:21:34,763
Goodness.

298
00:21:35,664 --> 00:21:37,499
I've been farming cabbage for years,

299
00:21:37,499 --> 00:21:39,701
but I've never seen or heard
anything like this.

300
00:21:40,002 --> 00:21:43,305
At this rate, we can't even
use fertilizer, let alone grow cabbage.

301
00:21:44,606 --> 00:21:46,775
You mean, all the other fields
are like this too?

302
00:21:47,076 --> 00:21:48,043
Goodness.

303
00:21:52,147 --> 00:21:53,382
Chief.

304
00:21:53,382 --> 00:21:55,117
There you are.

305
00:21:56,952 --> 00:21:58,387
I have a huge problem.

306
00:21:58,921 --> 00:22:01,090
The soil has gone bad.

307
00:22:01,090 --> 00:22:03,125
What am I going to do?

308
00:22:04,593 --> 00:22:05,627
Goodness.

309
00:22:12,668 --> 00:22:14,269
We must come up with a plan.

310
00:22:20,175 --> 00:22:21,443
Come on.

311
00:22:21,443 --> 00:22:24,613
This isn't the time to just sit around
in the village hall.

312
00:22:24,613 --> 00:22:27,616
Even Yong Cheol's field down there...

313
00:22:27,616 --> 00:22:29,718
has turned white.

314
00:22:30,419 --> 00:22:31,720
I've...

315
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,923
never seen anything like this
in my life.

316
00:22:34,923 --> 00:22:38,894
I thought someone dumped sugar
all over the ground...

317
00:22:38,894 --> 00:22:41,163
and almost tasted it.

318
00:22:41,964 --> 00:22:43,832
Who knew this could happen?

319
00:22:48,370 --> 00:22:49,671
This is horrible.

320
00:22:50,105 --> 00:22:51,039
I'll speak.

321
00:22:52,274 --> 00:22:53,375
Instead of sitting around like this,

322
00:22:53,375 --> 00:22:55,978
let's call the county office and get
a disinfection team out here.

323
00:22:55,978 --> 00:22:56,879
Yes.

324
00:22:56,879 --> 00:22:58,947
We must spray something strong...

325
00:22:58,947 --> 00:23:00,582
to kill all that white stuff, right?

326
00:23:01,617 --> 00:23:02,985
- I'll give them a call.
- Yes, do that.

327
00:23:02,985 --> 00:23:04,219
I know who to call.

328
00:23:06,121 --> 00:23:07,356
No.

329
00:23:08,123 --> 00:23:09,691
You can't call the disinfection team.

330
00:23:09,691 --> 00:23:10,926
Why not?

331
00:23:11,326 --> 00:23:14,029
If there are pests,
we must spray something.

332
00:23:14,029 --> 00:23:16,398
We can't just sit around and watch.

333
00:23:16,899 --> 00:23:19,568
If we spray chemicals without knowing
what that is,

334
00:23:19,568 --> 00:23:22,104
we'll kill all the beneficial microbes
in the soil too.

335
00:23:22,671 --> 00:23:25,407
Then the fields in Yeonri-ri
could become dead soil...

336
00:23:25,407 --> 00:23:27,042
where nothing will grow again.

337
00:23:27,843 --> 00:23:29,912
Then what are we supposed to do?

338
00:23:29,912 --> 00:23:33,382
That white stuff is eating the soil away.

339
00:23:33,382 --> 00:23:35,451
Should we just sit here and pray?

340
00:23:35,684 --> 00:23:37,419
Do you have any real solution?

341
00:23:37,419 --> 00:23:38,554
- Do you?
- Do you?

342
00:23:39,488 --> 00:23:40,389
Do you?

343
00:23:41,056 --> 00:23:42,491
I guess not.

344
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,795
Chief, we're going to the county office.

345
00:23:46,795 --> 00:23:47,830
Let's go.

346
00:23:47,830 --> 00:23:49,898
Let's go.

347
00:23:49,898 --> 00:23:53,168
We have to go.

348
00:23:53,836 --> 00:23:54,770
But...

349
00:23:56,605 --> 00:23:58,807
These fields are their livelihood.

350
00:23:59,374 --> 00:24:01,443
I get what you're saying,

351
00:24:01,443 --> 00:24:03,245
but those people can't see straight
right now.

352
00:24:04,446 --> 00:24:05,314
I'll...

353
00:24:06,915 --> 00:24:08,717
try to resolve this.

354
00:24:08,717 --> 00:24:11,153
What are you going to do?
Inspect it with a magnifying glass?

355
00:24:11,954 --> 00:24:14,289
I'll figure something out somehow.

356
00:24:14,823 --> 00:24:17,659
So please buy me some time...

357
00:24:17,659 --> 00:24:18,927
and stop them from calling
the disinfection team.

358
00:24:19,495 --> 00:24:20,763
If I can buy you some time,

359
00:24:23,165 --> 00:24:24,166
can you figure out...

360
00:24:26,368 --> 00:24:27,703
what caused this?

361
00:24:31,373 --> 00:24:32,307
I'll be sure...

362
00:24:33,776 --> 00:24:36,178
to restore those fields.

363
00:24:42,217 --> 00:24:45,287
(Kang Man Gap)

364
00:24:51,994 --> 00:24:53,629
(Kang Man Gap)

365
00:24:54,430 --> 00:24:56,899
I don't know what you are,

366
00:24:58,434 --> 00:25:00,769
but I'm Seong Tae Hun.

367
00:25:03,472 --> 00:25:04,773
The god of research.

368
00:25:04,773 --> 00:25:07,142
(Go Ok Sun)

369
00:25:08,143 --> 00:25:10,512
The embodiment of persistence and grit.

370
00:25:10,512 --> 00:25:12,147
(Jang Pil Sun)

371
00:25:12,147 --> 00:25:14,283
I've got pride in my life as a researcher.

372
00:25:15,417 --> 00:25:18,954
Just you watch.
I'll get to the bottom of it.

373
00:25:30,699 --> 00:25:34,269
(Seong Ji Sang's, don't touch)

374
00:25:47,182 --> 00:25:48,951
Hey, Wu Ju.

375
00:25:50,319 --> 00:25:53,188
What's going on? That's my pot.

376
00:25:53,655 --> 00:25:54,590
I know.

377
00:25:55,090 --> 00:25:57,493
Look. Yours is the only one that's green.

378
00:25:58,627 --> 00:26:01,029
I think you have a knack for farming.

379
00:26:03,665 --> 00:26:04,767
Do I?

380
00:26:06,402 --> 00:26:08,337
I'm good with shovels too.

381
00:26:09,505 --> 00:26:10,406
You are?

382
00:26:10,806 --> 00:26:13,542
I think farmers are the coolest
in the world.

383
00:26:14,309 --> 00:26:15,477
Really?

384
00:26:15,911 --> 00:26:17,546
You like farmers?

385
00:26:17,846 --> 00:26:18,747
Totally.

386
00:26:19,782 --> 00:26:22,518
They grow all kinds of things
from empty land.

387
00:26:24,086 --> 00:26:25,053
Like magic.

388
00:26:28,957 --> 00:26:29,992
Like magic.

389
00:26:36,331 --> 00:26:37,199
Magic...

390
00:26:38,700 --> 00:26:39,802
Like magic.

391
00:26:42,871 --> 00:26:45,107
Can I post this on Instagram?

392
00:26:46,008 --> 00:26:47,943
Yes, of course.

393
00:26:48,377 --> 00:26:49,478
Then...

394
00:26:50,412 --> 00:26:52,381
can you give me your ID?

395
00:26:59,121 --> 00:27:00,522
(Follow)

396
00:27:00,522 --> 00:27:01,723
(Following)

397
00:27:01,723 --> 00:27:02,591
Here.

398
00:27:04,993 --> 00:27:05,861
Thanks.

399
00:27:11,200 --> 00:27:12,868
Have a good break.

400
00:27:12,868 --> 00:27:14,303
You're leaving? Okay.

401
00:27:14,303 --> 00:27:15,270
Bye.

402
00:27:18,540 --> 00:27:19,441
Wait up.

403
00:27:21,110 --> 00:27:22,177
Wu Ju.

404
00:27:23,645 --> 00:27:26,882
(Cafeteria)

405
00:27:29,284 --> 00:27:30,152
Bo Mi.

406
00:27:30,986 --> 00:27:32,955
What are you doing during break?

407
00:27:34,022 --> 00:27:36,859
I have to go
to weekly training sessions...

408
00:27:36,859 --> 00:27:38,293
and develop new menu items.

409
00:27:38,794 --> 00:27:39,728
I have a lot to do.

410
00:27:41,530 --> 00:27:43,232
The marigold seeds you gave me...

411
00:27:44,099 --> 00:27:45,167
I planted them in a pot.

412
00:27:47,002 --> 00:27:47,970
Already?

413
00:27:48,570 --> 00:27:49,338
Yes.

414
00:27:49,772 --> 00:27:52,040
I kept it inside
because it may get too cold.

415
00:27:52,841 --> 00:27:55,043
But when I left, I put it in the backyard,

416
00:27:55,511 --> 00:27:56,678
so it can get sunlight.

417
00:27:57,012 --> 00:27:58,247
I want it to grow quickly.

418
00:27:59,314 --> 00:28:01,049
What's the rush?

419
00:28:01,049 --> 00:28:03,685
Just because you plant it,
doesn't mean it'll grow right away.

420
00:28:04,920 --> 00:28:06,922
I've always been interested in plants,

421
00:28:07,389 --> 00:28:08,924
but I've never actually grown one.

422
00:28:09,792 --> 00:28:10,692
So...

423
00:28:11,360 --> 00:28:14,329
I keep wondering if I watered it too much,

424
00:28:15,030 --> 00:28:16,732
or if there is something wrong
with the soil.

425
00:28:17,499 --> 00:28:19,368
I keep checking on it.

426
00:28:20,736 --> 00:28:21,603
It feels like...

427
00:28:23,072 --> 00:28:26,308
studying for a test with no answers.

428
00:28:27,376 --> 00:28:29,845
How is soil anything like studying?

429
00:28:30,512 --> 00:28:33,882
Don't worry. Just trust it and wait.

430
00:28:33,882 --> 00:28:35,284
Then it'll grow in its own time.

431
00:28:35,717 --> 00:28:36,685
I'm sure of it.

432
00:28:38,787 --> 00:28:41,757
All right. I'll try to be patient.

433
00:28:41,757 --> 00:28:42,624
Okay.

434
00:28:56,772 --> 00:28:57,639
Are you...

435
00:28:58,874 --> 00:29:00,375
still afraid of knives?

436
00:29:03,345 --> 00:29:04,346
Honestly,

437
00:29:07,483 --> 00:29:10,085
I get scared every time I hold a knife.

438
00:29:13,922 --> 00:29:16,158
I'm afraid I'll mess something up again.

439
00:29:19,394 --> 00:29:20,295
It's all right.

440
00:29:21,263 --> 00:29:23,799
This knife is a kind one.

441
00:29:27,369 --> 00:29:30,606
A knife can be kind?

442
00:29:31,373 --> 00:29:32,274
Yes.

443
00:29:32,274 --> 00:29:34,209
Yes. You must use it to cook food.

444
00:29:34,710 --> 00:29:36,979
And food saves people.

445
00:29:39,548 --> 00:29:41,350
Saves people?

446
00:29:42,885 --> 00:29:43,952
Well...

447
00:29:44,553 --> 00:29:46,388
Surgery isn't the only way to save people.

448
00:29:47,122 --> 00:29:49,057
A warm meal can save someone...

449
00:29:49,825 --> 00:29:51,427
and give people the strength
to live another day.

450
00:29:52,761 --> 00:29:54,930
So in a way,

451
00:29:54,930 --> 00:29:57,032
what we do is really meaningful.

452
00:30:26,361 --> 00:30:27,329
You're good.

453
00:30:39,508 --> 00:30:40,476
Would it be okay...

454
00:30:41,744 --> 00:30:45,714
to go to Mak Rae's place
to get my suitcase back?

455
00:30:46,448 --> 00:30:49,284
Why? Are you uncomfortable here?

456
00:30:52,488 --> 00:30:55,057
I just feel bad staying here and imposing.

457
00:30:55,824 --> 00:30:57,292
Don't be.

458
00:30:57,793 --> 00:31:01,363
Even if you stayed here for a year,
it'd be fine.

459
00:31:03,031 --> 00:31:06,468
Your kids have their father, right?

460
00:31:07,436 --> 00:31:08,604
Right?

461
00:31:08,604 --> 00:31:10,439
Yes, of course.

462
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:12,274
Yes.

463
00:31:13,275 --> 00:31:15,144
I'm home.

464
00:31:15,144 --> 00:31:16,278
You're home?

465
00:31:21,016 --> 00:31:24,219
Would you like some dumplings?

466
00:31:24,820 --> 00:31:26,855
They were just freshly steamed.

467
00:31:27,222 --> 00:31:28,223
Dumplings?

468
00:31:34,096 --> 00:31:36,198
- Dumplings?
- Dumplings.

469
00:31:36,732 --> 00:31:38,667
School's on break starting today.

470
00:31:38,667 --> 00:31:41,070
So while cleaning up the cafeteria,
we had some ingredients left.

471
00:31:42,404 --> 00:31:44,239
Do you not like dumplings?

472
00:31:45,707 --> 00:31:46,942
I do like them.

473
00:31:47,676 --> 00:31:49,178
Then try some.

474
00:31:49,178 --> 00:31:50,279
Yes.

475
00:31:50,279 --> 00:31:52,848
Try some.

476
00:31:52,848 --> 00:31:53,649
Okay.

477
00:32:03,892 --> 00:32:04,927
It's good.

478
00:32:07,496 --> 00:32:09,832
Who made these?

479
00:32:10,099 --> 00:32:12,534
These definitely don't look like
you made them.

480
00:32:14,503 --> 00:32:15,537
They taste different too.

481
00:32:16,872 --> 00:32:17,940
Well...

482
00:32:17,940 --> 00:32:19,708
I made them with Ji Cheon.

483
00:32:22,411 --> 00:32:23,245
What?

484
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,547
Is that so?

485
00:32:25,547 --> 00:32:28,684
Yes. He said he always wanted
to try making dumplings.

486
00:32:32,421 --> 00:32:34,890
Ji Cheon made dumplings?

487
00:32:39,394 --> 00:32:41,764
But what did you put in them?

488
00:32:41,764 --> 00:32:45,634
They taste different from the ones
you usually make.

489
00:32:45,634 --> 00:32:48,404
Ji Cheon suggested that instead of
just chives,

490
00:32:48,404 --> 00:32:50,005
we should add some bell peppers too.

491
00:32:50,005 --> 00:32:51,140
Lightly stir-fried.

492
00:32:51,140 --> 00:32:53,308
He comes up with ideas like this
very often.

493
00:32:55,477 --> 00:32:57,579
He knows his stuff.

494
00:33:08,290 --> 00:33:09,158
What?

495
00:33:11,126 --> 00:33:12,628
That punk.

496
00:33:13,095 --> 00:33:15,664
Did he quit med school
just to make dumplings?

497
00:33:16,832 --> 00:33:18,367
And why is it so annoyingly good?

498
00:33:19,401 --> 00:33:20,569
Unbelievable.

499
00:33:21,236 --> 00:33:24,706
Anyway, did Ji Sang and Ji Gu
finish the semester well?

500
00:33:25,941 --> 00:33:27,643
Goodness.

501
00:33:30,746 --> 00:33:33,582
Come out now. You should eat dinner.

502
00:33:35,751 --> 00:33:37,119
By the way,

503
00:33:38,921 --> 00:33:43,358
I heard Bo Mi studied food and nutrition.

504
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,727
Yes, she did.

505
00:33:46,361 --> 00:33:48,297
She even graduated top of her department.

506
00:33:49,064 --> 00:33:50,365
Don't you feel like it's a waste?

507
00:33:51,433 --> 00:33:53,135
Of course I do.

508
00:33:53,368 --> 00:33:55,270
We fought so much over it.

509
00:33:55,904 --> 00:33:58,974
I told her to go out into the big world
and really make something of herself.

510
00:33:59,641 --> 00:34:01,043
But this girl...

511
00:34:02,044 --> 00:34:04,747
made her own decision
and stood her ground.

512
00:34:06,081 --> 00:34:07,149
How could I possibly win against that?

513
00:34:08,817 --> 00:34:11,787
But shouldn't you win at least once,

514
00:34:11,787 --> 00:34:14,022
for her sake, so she can live better?
You're her mom.

515
00:34:14,790 --> 00:34:16,091
Just because I'm her mom,

516
00:34:16,692 --> 00:34:18,694
does that mean I have
the blueprint of her life?

517
00:34:24,166 --> 00:34:26,535
I tried everything too.

518
00:34:27,202 --> 00:34:29,605
"Listen to me. Do it my way."

519
00:34:30,773 --> 00:34:31,940
But in the end,

520
00:34:32,808 --> 00:34:35,010
Bo Mi felt suffocated,

521
00:34:36,478 --> 00:34:40,015
and I was rotting away inside too.

522
00:34:43,685 --> 00:34:45,621
Don't think of them as your kids.

523
00:34:46,455 --> 00:34:48,257
Think of them as boarders.
It's easier that way.

524
00:34:48,757 --> 00:34:50,926
- Boarders?
- Yes.

525
00:34:50,926 --> 00:34:52,828
Someone who lives under your roof,

526
00:34:52,828 --> 00:34:54,663
but you have no control over.

527
00:34:57,332 --> 00:34:59,701
You treat them like valued guests,

528
00:35:00,803 --> 00:35:03,605
but don't tell them...

529
00:35:05,274 --> 00:35:06,575
how to live their lives.

530
00:35:10,112 --> 00:35:12,448
Come on. Let's go eat.

531
00:35:14,316 --> 00:35:15,417
Let's eat.

532
00:35:17,853 --> 00:35:19,121
But he's my son.

533
00:35:20,656 --> 00:35:21,924
Forget it.

534
00:35:48,717 --> 00:35:50,219
Mat Story research lab.

535
00:35:50,219 --> 00:35:53,055
Hello. This is Manager Seong Tae Hun
from the Yeonri-ri branch.

536
00:35:54,156 --> 00:35:56,592
I'd like to send a few samples...

537
00:35:56,592 --> 00:35:59,495
and request a detailed analysis
using headquarters' equipment.

538
00:35:59,995 --> 00:36:02,531
From Yeonri-ri?
Are these seedling samples?

539
00:36:03,198 --> 00:36:06,201
No. This is an unidentified fungus...

540
00:36:06,201 --> 00:36:08,170
spreading across the soil in Yeonri-ri.

541
00:36:08,604 --> 00:36:10,939
I'll include soil samples
from the origin point...

542
00:36:13,041 --> 00:36:15,010
I sent you a little gift.

543
00:36:17,012 --> 00:36:18,981
A gift?

544
00:36:19,982 --> 00:36:20,949
Mr. Choi.

545
00:36:21,817 --> 00:36:22,985
The sample analysis report.

546
00:36:23,852 --> 00:36:24,753
What is this?

547
00:36:25,421 --> 00:36:27,623
What's this?

548
00:36:28,624 --> 00:36:30,692
This is ridiculous.

549
00:36:33,262 --> 00:36:34,296
Mr. Seong Tae Hun?

550
00:36:35,531 --> 00:36:37,499
Yes? Never mind.

551
00:36:37,499 --> 00:36:40,169
Now that I think about it,
there's something I must double-check.

552
00:36:40,836 --> 00:36:43,472
I'll call you back later. Bye.

553
00:36:55,417 --> 00:36:56,952
I can't leave this to headquarters.

554
00:36:58,020 --> 00:36:59,088
I have to do it myself.

555
00:37:00,389 --> 00:37:01,256
Me.

556
00:37:02,391 --> 00:37:03,392
(National Agricultural Science
and Technology)

557
00:37:03,392 --> 00:37:05,094
When will the results be ready?

558
00:37:05,094 --> 00:37:07,896
Is there any way to speed it up?

559
00:37:07,896 --> 00:37:10,866
It's like the whole village was given
a death sentence.

560
00:37:10,866 --> 00:37:12,835
That's tough.

561
00:37:13,135 --> 00:37:16,371
We'll do our best to find out
as quickly as possible.

562
00:37:19,241 --> 00:37:20,242
Here you go.

563
00:37:20,242 --> 00:37:21,076
Thank you.

564
00:37:23,846 --> 00:37:28,884
(National Agricultural Science
and Technology)

565
00:37:33,222 --> 00:37:36,391
(Receipt, soil analysis request received)

566
00:37:48,470 --> 00:37:50,906
You're supposed to become a doctor.

567
00:37:51,540 --> 00:37:53,242
So what is there for you to learn here?

568
00:37:55,477 --> 00:37:56,678
Mom.

569
00:37:56,678 --> 00:37:58,814
You said you're short-handed.

570
00:37:59,948 --> 00:38:02,050
Ji Cheon is really capable...

571
00:38:02,050 --> 00:38:03,485
and hardworking.

572
00:38:03,485 --> 00:38:04,720
You stay out of this.

573
00:38:05,287 --> 00:38:07,356
Can't he speak for himself?

574
00:38:09,691 --> 00:38:10,959
I dropped out of med school,

575
00:38:11,860 --> 00:38:13,796
and I want to find
what I'm actually good at.

576
00:38:13,796 --> 00:38:15,230
Until then, I want to do whatever I can.

577
00:38:16,198 --> 00:38:18,434
If you give me the chance, I'll work hard.

578
00:38:27,176 --> 00:38:28,010
Goodness.

579
00:38:28,877 --> 00:38:30,579
- Hello.
- Goodness.

580
00:38:30,579 --> 00:38:32,414
I ran into the delivery driver out front.

581
00:38:32,414 --> 00:38:34,383
They must be heavy.

582
00:38:34,383 --> 00:38:36,118
- Bring them inside please.
- Okay.

583
00:38:36,118 --> 00:38:38,787
You're so manly, Officer Park.

584
00:38:39,388 --> 00:38:40,289
Iced Americano?

585
00:38:40,289 --> 00:38:42,324
Yes, thank you.
With an extra shot, please.

586
00:38:42,758 --> 00:38:43,592
Bo Mi.

587
00:38:46,895 --> 00:38:47,996
You're here too, Ji Cheon.

588
00:38:49,832 --> 00:38:50,666
I'll carry them.

589
00:38:51,066 --> 00:38:53,068
Those hands are meant for studying.
You don't want to injure them.

590
00:38:54,169 --> 00:38:55,971
I'm working here for a while.
Give them to me.

591
00:39:00,576 --> 00:39:01,510
See? They're heavy, right?

592
00:39:02,411 --> 00:39:03,245
I said I'd do it.

593
00:39:06,248 --> 00:39:08,117
No. They're not that heavy.

594
00:39:20,763 --> 00:39:23,332
Seong Ji Sang, fold your own clothes.

595
00:39:26,235 --> 00:39:29,138
Ji Cheon, I grew this sprout myself.

596
00:39:30,472 --> 00:39:31,774
Isn't it nice and green?

597
00:39:33,041 --> 00:39:34,176
This one's yours too, right?

598
00:39:35,677 --> 00:39:37,212
She said I did a good job.

599
00:39:38,614 --> 00:39:40,282
That I've got a farmer's talent.

600
00:39:40,983 --> 00:39:41,817
Who said that?

601
00:39:42,651 --> 00:39:43,485
Wu Ju.

602
00:39:44,286 --> 00:39:45,120
Han Wu Ju.

603
00:39:45,821 --> 00:39:48,590
She's Wu Ju, and I'm Ji Sang.

604
00:39:49,491 --> 00:39:50,826
It's destiny.

605
00:39:51,994 --> 00:39:53,462
It's fate.

606
00:39:58,333 --> 00:39:59,435
Magic.

607
00:39:59,435 --> 00:40:01,403
This is really magic.

608
00:40:01,403 --> 00:40:03,439
There's no other way to explain it.

609
00:40:05,040 --> 00:40:07,409
Ji Cheon, I'm cold.

610
00:40:08,844 --> 00:40:10,145
I'm cold.

611
00:40:11,246 --> 00:40:12,114
You're cold?

612
00:40:15,384 --> 00:40:18,287
I'm cold.

613
00:40:18,821 --> 00:40:20,055
I turned up the heat already.

614
00:40:21,690 --> 00:40:23,625
When is Mom coming back?

615
00:40:25,761 --> 00:40:27,663
Soon. Hang in there.

616
00:40:28,864 --> 00:40:31,400
That's what you always say.

617
00:40:31,400 --> 00:40:33,402
I miss Mom.

618
00:40:35,370 --> 00:40:36,405
Let's go to sleep now.

619
00:40:36,872 --> 00:40:38,741
I'll come sleep next to you.

620
00:40:40,375 --> 00:40:42,044
Seong Ji Sang. Come lie down next to him.

621
00:40:43,912 --> 00:40:44,980
Come on.

622
00:40:45,881 --> 00:40:47,116
I run hot,

623
00:40:47,116 --> 00:40:48,650
so I hate people being too close to me.

624
00:41:04,700 --> 00:41:06,001
It's cramped.

625
00:41:58,954 --> 00:42:00,189
They're all the same.

626
00:42:06,328 --> 00:42:09,364
(Fibrous ring, radial spread,
same soil depth)

627
00:42:23,011 --> 00:42:24,546
It doesn't smell like fertilizer.

628
00:42:26,081 --> 00:42:27,049
A virus?

629
00:42:28,550 --> 00:42:29,384
A fungus?

630
00:42:30,652 --> 00:42:32,988
Why did this suddenly appear
across the entire village?

631
00:42:39,061 --> 00:42:40,763
If we spray chemicals
without knowing what it is,

632
00:42:41,196 --> 00:42:43,665
it could completely change
the soil environment.

633
00:42:45,501 --> 00:42:47,569
But we can't just sit back and do nothing.

634
00:42:56,345 --> 00:42:59,648
Abnormal soil conditions in winter.

635
00:43:02,284 --> 00:43:05,087
(An invisible danger,
a warning of winter soil disease)

636
00:43:05,087 --> 00:43:07,589
(It's invisible, but it is one of
the deadliest threats to farms.)

637
00:43:11,493 --> 00:43:13,595
Where did this even start?

638
00:43:16,398 --> 00:43:17,933
What's the cause?

639
00:43:19,868 --> 00:43:20,736
The cause.

640
00:43:40,422 --> 00:43:42,324
The surface temperature
is clearly below freezing.

641
00:43:42,891 --> 00:43:44,660
But the organism is surviving?

642
00:43:45,928 --> 00:43:47,062
What's the reason?

643
00:43:50,933 --> 00:43:51,934
Let's check the ground temperature first.

644
00:44:00,142 --> 00:44:01,844
Why is he digging
in the middle of the night?

645
00:44:02,611 --> 00:44:04,046
Even ghosts would freeze
and run away in this cold.

646
00:44:05,948 --> 00:44:07,716
It's cold out here.

647
00:44:09,017 --> 00:44:11,286
What are you doing with a pickaxe
at this hour?

648
00:44:12,387 --> 00:44:13,288
Well...

649
00:44:14,690 --> 00:44:16,391
I thought it was strange...

650
00:44:16,391 --> 00:44:18,060
that the fungus was spreading in winter,

651
00:44:18,060 --> 00:44:20,529
so I'm checking the ground temperature
under the mulch first.

652
00:44:22,030 --> 00:44:23,298
Why are you going this far?

653
00:44:23,966 --> 00:44:25,968
I'm sure Mat Story didn't tell you
to do this.

654
00:44:27,469 --> 00:44:29,972
I'm doing this as a resident of Yeonri-ri,

655
00:44:29,972 --> 00:44:31,673
not as a Mat Story employee.

656
00:44:36,011 --> 00:44:37,980
Go inside and rest. I'll do it.

657
00:44:37,980 --> 00:44:39,915
No, I can do it.

658
00:44:39,915 --> 00:44:42,117
I'll dig from here to there,

659
00:44:42,117 --> 00:44:43,519
so get inside and warm up your hands.

660
00:44:43,519 --> 00:44:44,753
You'll kill yourself digging like that.

661
00:44:44,753 --> 00:44:46,088
I'm fine.

662
00:44:46,088 --> 00:44:48,457
I've used a pickaxe in the army.

663
00:44:48,457 --> 00:44:50,726
You said so yourself
that you're a resident of Yeonri-ri.

664
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:54,029
If a villager is digging all night,

665
00:44:54,029 --> 00:44:55,631
how can I, the village chief,
sit and do nothing?

666
00:44:55,631 --> 00:44:57,299
What kind of chief would I be?
I'd be useless.

667
00:44:59,501 --> 00:45:01,070
You're so stubborn.

668
00:45:02,004 --> 00:45:04,073
Your digging sounded so bad...

669
00:45:04,073 --> 00:45:06,141
that I couldn't sleep.
That's why I came out.

670
00:45:08,744 --> 00:45:10,412
Go ahead and dig then.

671
00:45:10,412 --> 00:45:11,080
All right.

672
00:45:14,850 --> 00:45:17,753
The soil won't turn over
because you're not doing it right.

673
00:45:17,753 --> 00:45:19,054
It's frozen solid.

674
00:45:20,489 --> 00:45:23,292
It's been ages since you went to the army.
Why are you still going on about it?

675
00:45:23,292 --> 00:45:24,993
I'm sure you just pushed a pen around
or something.

676
00:45:24,993 --> 00:45:26,895
You're so chatty.
I wish I could sew your mouth shut.

677
00:45:26,895 --> 00:45:28,730
It's completely frozen solid.

678
00:45:50,385 --> 00:45:51,520
My back.

679
00:46:02,865 --> 00:46:06,135
I just want one day off.

680
00:46:06,135 --> 00:46:08,971
Just one day.

681
00:46:13,842 --> 00:46:17,112
I will rewrite the report.

682
00:46:17,112 --> 00:46:20,015
Based on facts with reliable data.

683
00:46:20,649 --> 00:46:22,251
Yes, of course.

684
00:46:23,051 --> 00:46:25,421
Of course it should be written
based on facts.

685
00:46:25,421 --> 00:46:26,688
Follow your convictions.

686
00:46:33,429 --> 00:46:34,363
Yes.

687
00:46:39,001 --> 00:46:40,335
I have my convictions.

688
00:46:41,103 --> 00:46:42,337
If I don't do anything,

689
00:46:42,871 --> 00:46:45,107
even if Yeonri-ri's cabbage
gets disqualified,

690
00:46:45,574 --> 00:46:46,809
I'll have nothing to say.

691
00:46:47,176 --> 00:46:49,812
Yes. I must get up.

692
00:46:49,812 --> 00:46:50,679
Get up.

693
00:47:09,998 --> 00:47:10,899
My back.

694
00:47:12,901 --> 00:47:14,870
What are you doing? Making breakfast?

695
00:47:15,537 --> 00:47:17,039
I cooked some soup last night.

696
00:47:17,039 --> 00:47:18,107
We just need to heat it up.

697
00:47:18,574 --> 00:47:20,409
Ji Gu has a pretty high fever right now.

698
00:47:20,409 --> 00:47:21,944
I'm going to give him some porridge
and take him to the hospital.

699
00:47:22,678 --> 00:47:24,012
Is it bad?

700
00:47:24,213 --> 00:47:26,815
Yes. He was moaning all night,
asking for Mom.

701
00:47:27,649 --> 00:47:29,318
He's been holding it in all this time.

702
00:47:33,055 --> 00:47:34,456
Mom.

703
00:47:37,359 --> 00:47:39,428
Mom.

704
00:47:39,428 --> 00:47:40,763
He's burning up.

705
00:47:40,763 --> 00:47:42,698
Wake up. Ji Gu, wake up.

706
00:47:42,698 --> 00:47:44,533
Wake up.

707
00:47:44,533 --> 00:47:46,602
Ji Gu, wake up.

708
00:47:46,602 --> 00:47:47,469
Wake up.

709
00:47:48,504 --> 00:47:49,438
What do I do?

710
00:47:50,105 --> 00:47:52,207
What do I do?

711
00:47:52,207 --> 00:47:54,276
What do I do?

712
00:47:54,676 --> 00:47:56,645
Ji Gu, don't cry.

713
00:47:57,346 --> 00:47:59,948
- Don't go, Mom.
- Wake up.

714
00:48:02,985 --> 00:48:06,121
Why did you go out at night
and put yourself through all that?

715
00:48:07,456 --> 00:48:08,524
Be gentle.

716
00:48:08,991 --> 00:48:10,759
If I left Tae Hun out there alone,

717
00:48:10,759 --> 00:48:12,561
he would've frozen to death digging.

718
00:48:13,896 --> 00:48:17,399
At your age, you should know
to take care of yourself.

719
00:48:17,699 --> 00:48:21,070
The only one who really looks out for me
is my Hye Sun.

720
00:48:21,070 --> 00:48:22,137
I love you.

721
00:48:22,137 --> 00:48:23,572
Stop it.

722
00:48:24,406 --> 00:48:25,374
That's gross.

723
00:48:27,576 --> 00:48:29,578
By the way,

724
00:48:30,079 --> 00:48:33,382
what are we going to do about
this problem in all these fields?

725
00:48:34,450 --> 00:48:36,085
I don't have time to be sitting around
like this.

726
00:48:37,019 --> 00:48:38,287
I should go out there.

727
00:48:38,287 --> 00:48:40,422
- There you go again.
- Mom. Dad.

728
00:48:41,256 --> 00:48:42,391
We have a problem.

729
00:48:42,391 --> 00:48:44,927
- What is it?
- What's the problem?

730
00:48:49,832 --> 00:48:51,834
Ji Gu is sick and has a fever.

731
00:48:52,735 --> 00:48:53,602
What?

732
00:48:54,436 --> 00:48:55,337
I...

733
00:49:00,008 --> 00:49:02,511
Shouldn't we go too?

734
00:49:03,011 --> 00:49:04,246
Mom.

735
00:49:04,246 --> 00:49:06,315
Mom, don't go.

736
00:49:07,716 --> 00:49:10,252
Ji Gu.

737
00:49:10,252 --> 00:49:12,054
Take a bite of this.

738
00:49:12,421 --> 00:49:14,389
- Then let's take your med.
- Just one bite.

739
00:49:15,257 --> 00:49:17,226
Hang in there. I'm coming.

740
00:49:19,495 --> 00:49:20,562
Mom.

741
00:49:21,997 --> 00:49:23,732
Don't cry. Mommy's here.

742
00:49:24,833 --> 00:49:25,834
Take one bite.

743
00:49:25,834 --> 00:49:26,702
Ji Gu.

744
00:49:28,003 --> 00:49:29,905
- Ji Gu.
- Honey.

745
00:49:29,905 --> 00:49:32,808
- Are you okay? Come here, Ji Gu.
- Honey.

746
00:49:38,514 --> 00:49:39,815
Mom.

747
00:49:41,583 --> 00:49:42,684
Honey.

748
00:49:42,684 --> 00:49:44,086
Mom.

749
00:49:45,020 --> 00:49:46,655
Yes, Mommy's here.

750
00:49:46,655 --> 00:49:48,891
Honey.

751
00:49:48,891 --> 00:49:50,125
I'm sorry.

752
00:49:50,125 --> 00:49:52,060
I'm sorry, Ji Gu.

753
00:49:55,197 --> 00:49:56,031
I'm sorry.

754
00:50:17,586 --> 00:50:18,487
Here.

755
00:50:20,522 --> 00:50:22,291
- Mom, it's cold.
- What?

756
00:50:23,392 --> 00:50:24,593
Just for a little bit.

757
00:50:24,993 --> 00:50:27,129
You'll feel better soon.

758
00:50:30,032 --> 00:50:30,866
Ji Gu.

759
00:50:34,870 --> 00:50:37,306
Let's take your med once more, Ji Gu.

760
00:50:38,073 --> 00:50:38,974
No.

761
00:50:39,575 --> 00:50:41,110
It'll make me drowsy.

762
00:50:41,844 --> 00:50:44,279
If I fall asleep, you'll leave.

763
00:50:48,050 --> 00:50:49,418
Mommy isn't going anywhere.

764
00:50:50,452 --> 00:50:52,488
So let's take your med, okay?

765
00:50:53,622 --> 00:50:54,556
Do you mean that?

766
00:51:01,797 --> 00:51:02,631
Yes.

767
00:51:03,866 --> 00:51:05,401
I'll be right here,

768
00:51:06,101 --> 00:51:07,302
so let's take the medicine.

769
00:51:12,975 --> 00:51:15,210
Ji Gu. She's staying, so take this.

770
00:51:15,210 --> 00:51:16,178
Open up.

771
00:51:16,178 --> 00:51:17,913
- Open.
- Open.

772
00:51:20,716 --> 00:51:21,850
There you go.

773
00:51:24,019 --> 00:51:26,922
Once more. Here.

774
00:51:28,624 --> 00:51:29,491
Good.

775
00:51:34,496 --> 00:51:35,364
Here.

776
00:51:52,514 --> 00:51:53,449
Well...

777
00:51:54,683 --> 00:51:55,918
Ji Gu's fever...

778
00:51:57,086 --> 00:51:59,254
has definitely gone down.

779
00:52:01,423 --> 00:52:02,224
Really?

780
00:52:03,092 --> 00:52:04,159
What a relief.

781
00:52:07,930 --> 00:52:09,765
After you came back home,

782
00:52:09,765 --> 00:52:10,899
you see...

783
00:52:10,899 --> 00:52:13,502
His breathing...

784
00:52:14,036 --> 00:52:15,771
sounded different. It was strange.

785
00:52:22,144 --> 00:52:23,312
Shall we sit for a bit?

786
00:52:24,179 --> 00:52:25,047
Yes.

787
00:52:44,900 --> 00:52:46,034
You see...

788
00:52:49,872 --> 00:52:50,839
All this time,

789
00:52:52,674 --> 00:52:57,146
I thought I was doing my best
in my own way.

790
00:52:59,214 --> 00:53:01,250
'I'm their mom, so I have to be strong.

791
00:53:02,217 --> 00:53:04,019
I shouldn't cause worry.'

792
00:53:08,223 --> 00:53:09,158
But...

793
00:53:10,526 --> 00:53:12,194
I think I was forcing it.

794
00:53:15,564 --> 00:53:16,665
Even...

795
00:53:17,733 --> 00:53:19,134
smiling...

796
00:53:20,636 --> 00:53:22,137
I had to make an effort.

797
00:53:23,672 --> 00:53:24,973
With you,

798
00:53:26,708 --> 00:53:27,743
and with the kids...

799
00:53:33,816 --> 00:53:35,684
I should act natural, right?

800
00:53:38,220 --> 00:53:39,354
Why was I...

801
00:53:41,390 --> 00:53:44,526
trying so hard,

802
00:53:45,260 --> 00:53:46,995
even with my own family?

803
00:53:49,565 --> 00:53:52,634
That's just how people live.

804
00:53:52,634 --> 00:53:54,703
How can everything always feel natural?

805
00:53:56,872 --> 00:53:58,774
But when I saw the chief's family,

806
00:54:00,175 --> 00:54:01,677
it all felt so natural.

807
00:54:02,878 --> 00:54:04,813
- Bo Mi, let's eat.
- Let's eat.

808
00:54:04,813 --> 00:54:07,216
I'm starving.

809
00:54:07,216 --> 00:54:09,818
I carried so many fertilizer bags.
My back is just...

810
00:54:10,452 --> 00:54:11,487
Goodness.

811
00:54:13,589 --> 00:54:14,456
Dad.

812
00:54:16,125 --> 00:54:18,193
Everything looked so comfortable.

813
00:54:19,661 --> 00:54:20,529
Hey, Im Bo Mi.

814
00:54:21,463 --> 00:54:23,298
Why are you stuck to her
like melted taffy in summer?

815
00:54:23,298 --> 00:54:24,700
Your mom must be hot. Move aside.

816
00:54:25,267 --> 00:54:26,668
No.

817
00:54:27,336 --> 00:54:28,837
Can't I do this? I just love Mom so much.

818
00:54:28,837 --> 00:54:31,306
Without forcing anything,

819
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:34,343
they were laughing
and trusting each other.

820
00:54:36,445 --> 00:54:37,513
That's how they were.

821
00:54:45,421 --> 00:54:48,123
I believed that working hard at my job...

822
00:54:49,425 --> 00:54:50,659
was the best thing I could do...

823
00:54:51,727 --> 00:54:53,629
for my family.

824
00:54:56,231 --> 00:54:57,266
But then I realized...

825
00:54:58,700 --> 00:55:01,036
that I wasn't really part of my family.

826
00:55:01,036 --> 00:55:03,872
I was just circling around outside it.

827
00:55:18,520 --> 00:55:19,421
So...

828
00:55:21,056 --> 00:55:22,391
I made you feel lonely.

829
00:55:25,461 --> 00:55:29,031
You probably had to carry a lot
on your own.

830
00:55:40,209 --> 00:55:41,110
I'm sorry.

831
00:55:42,845 --> 00:55:44,880
I was only thinking about doing my best...

832
00:55:46,648 --> 00:55:48,283
that I didn't see...

833
00:55:49,418 --> 00:55:50,452
how much you were enduring.

834
00:56:19,415 --> 00:56:20,282
Mom.

835
00:56:22,551 --> 00:56:23,519
You're up?

836
00:56:25,154 --> 00:56:26,288
How's Ji Gu?

837
00:56:27,556 --> 00:56:30,092
I just checked in on him.
I think his fever is gone now.

838
00:56:32,761 --> 00:56:34,630
Mom.

839
00:56:41,603 --> 00:56:44,740
I still don't fully understand you.

840
00:56:47,009 --> 00:56:49,611
You can think I'm narrow-minded
if you want.

841
00:56:50,612 --> 00:56:53,015
That's just the kind of person I am.

842
00:56:53,415 --> 00:56:55,117
That's not what I was trying to say.

843
00:56:57,553 --> 00:56:59,321
I want to talk with you.

844
00:57:17,239 --> 00:57:18,073
You...

845
00:57:18,507 --> 00:57:20,309
started working at that cafe...

846
00:57:20,309 --> 00:57:22,411
as soon as summer break began?

847
00:57:25,180 --> 00:57:27,249
When you made that decision,

848
00:57:27,950 --> 00:57:29,618
did you ever think about how I'd feel?

849
00:57:31,887 --> 00:57:34,523
If you had truly considered what I said,

850
00:57:34,523 --> 00:57:36,492
you wouldn't have made
that decision so easily.

851
00:57:38,127 --> 00:57:39,194
I want to show you...

852
00:57:40,662 --> 00:57:42,097
that I'm finding my own path.

853
00:57:44,900 --> 00:57:45,734
Just a little...

854
00:57:46,735 --> 00:57:48,537
Can you give me just a little time?

855
00:57:53,542 --> 00:57:55,677
"It's okay. I understand."

856
00:57:56,478 --> 00:57:58,080
I can't tell you those lies.

857
00:57:59,281 --> 00:58:00,582
I'm not going to pretend to try either.

858
00:58:03,185 --> 00:58:04,052
But...

859
00:58:06,321 --> 00:58:07,623
I'll take some time.

860
00:58:11,693 --> 00:58:14,062
So you should also think again...

861
00:58:14,062 --> 00:58:15,297
about the choice you made.

862
00:58:29,578 --> 00:58:30,813
So this is a report...

863
00:58:30,813 --> 00:58:33,182
from the National Agricultural Science
and Technology?

864
00:58:33,982 --> 00:58:36,385
It's a soil sample analysis report.

865
00:58:38,620 --> 00:58:39,488
Let's open it.

866
00:58:49,965 --> 00:58:51,600
I'm telling Mom.

867
00:58:51,600 --> 00:58:53,602
Go ahead.

868
00:58:54,970 --> 00:58:56,672
That tickles. Stop.

869
00:58:58,207 --> 00:58:59,241
Is anyone home?

870
00:59:00,375 --> 00:59:01,543
Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo.

871
00:59:02,010 --> 00:59:03,178
Yes?

872
00:59:03,178 --> 00:59:04,546
Is Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo home?

873
00:59:05,981 --> 00:59:07,449
Registered mail delivery.

874
00:59:13,155 --> 00:59:14,056
Okay.

875
00:59:15,491 --> 00:59:16,892
Yes, that's me.

876
00:59:16,892 --> 00:59:18,894
You are Ms. Cho Mi Ryeo, correct?

877
00:59:19,828 --> 00:59:21,463
This is a special court delivery.

878
00:59:23,699 --> 00:59:25,467
Please sign here.

879
00:59:26,502 --> 00:59:27,936
From the court to me?

880
00:59:27,936 --> 00:59:28,871
Yes, right here.

881
00:59:39,915 --> 00:59:40,816
Here you go.

882
00:59:41,617 --> 00:59:42,618
Goodbye.

883
00:59:56,165 --> 00:59:57,733
You reap...

884
00:59:59,168 --> 01:00:00,936
what you sow.

885
01:00:02,571 --> 01:00:04,907
A lawsuit to recover a loan?

886
01:00:04,907 --> 01:00:07,609
The simple truth of reaping
what you sow...

887
01:00:08,710 --> 01:00:11,947
Why didn't I truly understand that
back then?

888
01:00:12,648 --> 01:00:13,715
Where are you?

889
01:00:15,084 --> 01:00:16,952
Pay me back, you wench.

890
01:00:19,221 --> 01:00:21,890
You thought I wouldn't find you?

891
01:00:25,994 --> 01:00:28,630
You thought hiding in some rural town
in Korea would keep me from finding you?

892
01:00:30,532 --> 01:00:31,633
What's buried...

893
01:00:32,067 --> 01:00:34,737
will eventually grow.

894
01:00:37,406 --> 01:00:39,441
The deeper you try to bury it,

895
01:00:39,942 --> 01:00:41,510
the more powerfully it grows.

896
01:01:09,338 --> 01:01:12,341
(Cabbage Your Life)

897
01:01:12,341 --> 01:01:14,476
The flower of youth is blooming in full.

898
01:01:14,476 --> 01:01:15,978
It's out of my hands now.

899
01:01:15,978 --> 01:01:17,112
You've grown attached now?

900
01:01:17,112 --> 01:01:18,614
We're in the middle of developing
a new menu.

901
01:01:18,614 --> 01:01:20,282
Do you really need to be this close?

902
01:01:20,282 --> 01:01:21,750
Go home now. Hurry.

903
01:01:21,750 --> 01:01:23,552
I'm your husband.

904
01:01:23,552 --> 01:01:24,653
If anything gets too hard,

905
01:01:24,653 --> 01:01:26,422
let me know everything, okay?

906
01:01:26,688 --> 01:01:27,623
What am I going to do?

907
01:01:27,623 --> 01:01:31,760
I never thought things would
get out of hand like this.

908
01:01:31,760 --> 01:01:33,195
Didn't you hear that?

909
01:01:33,195 --> 01:01:34,830
What are you doing here?

910
01:01:34,830 --> 01:01:36,899
Have you noticed anything unusual...

911
01:01:36,899 --> 01:01:38,267
around Yeonri-ri lately?

912
01:01:38,267 --> 01:01:40,035
Why is this spreading only in Yeonri-ri?

913
01:01:40,035 --> 01:01:42,438
What on earth is driving you?

914
01:01:42,438 --> 01:01:43,338
Could that be it?

915
01:01:44,901 --> 01:01:46,901
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
